      <head id="a1">DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY</head>
      <unittitle encodinganalog="MARC 245" label="Title:">Women's Roller Derby collection, </unittitle><unitdate certainty="approximate" encodinganalog="MARC 245" type="inclusive">2000-2012.</unitdate>
      <unitid label="Collection Number:">8090</unitid>
      <origination label="Creator:"/>
      <physdesc encodinganalog="MARC 300" label="Quantity:"><extent>3 cubic feet</extent></physdesc>
      <physdesc label="Forms of Material:">Printed material</physdesc>
      <repository label="Repository:">Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell
        University Library</repository>
      <abstract label="Abstract:">The collection consists of ephemera relating to over 19 women's
        roller derby leagues leagues, both flat track and banked track. </abstract>
      <langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English</language></langmaterial>
    </did>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
      <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
      <p>The collection consists of 252 posters, 46 programs, 24 flyers, 28 team stickers, 13
        postcards, 1 magnet, and 1 calendar. Included are posters promoting bouts, fliers,
        handbills, logos, stickers, photographs, schedules, programs, and a calendar. Materials
        feature striking graphic design, and information such as team names, schedules, places,
        dates, sponsors, and websites. Over 19 leagues are represented, both flat track and banked
        track. Among the teams represented are: Naptown Rollergirls, Lone Star Rollergirls,
        Providence Roller Derby, Dallas Derby Devils, Rose City Rollers, Down South Derby, The
        Cincinnati Rollergirls, North Kentucky Roller Derby, Black-N-Bluegrass Roller Derby, Kansas
        City Roller Derby, Bleeding Heartland Rollergirls, Central Coast Roller Derby, Echo City
        Knockouts (Hawaii), ICT Rollergirls, Rat City Rollergirls, and Arizona Roller Derby, among
        others.</p>
    </scopecontent>
